    "extras": [
      "Buy the Jordan Pass before arrival: Wanderer ₹8,260, Explorer ₹8,850 and Expert ₹9,440. All waive the 40 JOD visa fee if you stay at least 2 nights and cover Petra, Jerash, Wadi Rum, Amman Citadel, Mount Nebo and many other sites.",
      "JETT is the most reliable public transport for tourist corridors, but most routes run only once daily, so pre-book Petra, Wadi Rum and Aqaba legs.",
      "Petra by Night is never included in the Jordan Pass, and Bethany Beyond the Jordan typically remains a separate paid ticket.",
      "If you self-drive, the Desert Highway is faster while the King's Highway is more scenic via Madaba, Kerak and canyon viewpoints.",
      "Wadi Rum camps usually bundle dinner and breakfast, but jeep tours, camel rides and star-gazing add-ons are normally cash-first.",
      "At the Dead Sea, avoid shaving the same day, keep the water out of your eyes, and shower quickly after the float because the salt sting is real."
    ],
